com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Class AdobePSDMutableLayerNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePSDLayerNode
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePSDMutableLayerNode

  • public class AdobePSDMutableLayerNode
extends AdobePSDLayerNode
    This class allows you to create (or edit) the properties for a layer node. Examples would be creating layer groups, RGB pixel layers, etc.

        public AdobePSDMutableLayerNode(java.lang.String name,
                                com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.psd.AdobePSDLayerNodeType type)
        Construct a new layer node with name and type.

        Note: The newly initialized layer node does not yet have a valid layerId. Its layerId gets set when it gets added to the PSD composite.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the new layer node.
        type - the type of the new layer node.
